response:
Use the /v1/orders API with the CancelSubscription order action. In the processingOptions of the cancellation, configure the refund parameters.

Payload Snippet:
json
"cancelSubscription": {
    "processingOptions": {
        "runBilling": true,
        "collectPayment": false,
        "refund": true,
        "writeOff": true,
        "refundAmount": "10.00"
    }
}

Note: You cannot override the Refund Reason Code in this API call; it will use the default.

You can update the Account.InvoiceTemplateId field using custom logic. This is commonly done in production environments. For example, you can use JavaScript in a custom function to map Communication Profile IDs to Invoice Template IDs. Here is a sample code snippet:

const map = {
  '8a28eb6e7572f46d0175755770803a17': '8a28a00578f3819d0178f48651c50c33', //Dutch
  '8a28eb68836a0c0d01838e54f4b325d8': '8a288b2978f381a30178f483112b63d7', //English
  // ... add other mappings
};
if (account.Batch == "Batch1") {
  var templateId = map[account.CommunicationProfileId];
  if (templateId) {
    return ({ success: true, message: 'Assigning template ' + templateId, data: { InvoiceTemplateId: templateId } });
  } else {
    return ({ success: true, message: 'Cannot map the template.' });
  }
} else {
  return ({ success: true });
}

Alternatively, you can use a Decision Table to achieve the same mapping by setting the InvoiceTemplateId based on the CommunicationProfileId or other criteria. Hardcoded values for template IDs are often used, but be aware that these IDs may differ between environments.
